President Biden gave a speech at the Sheraton Philadelphia Downtown, expressing gratitude to the attendees for their support and highlighting the importance of Philadelphia in his political career. He mentioned his wife's love for the Philadelphia Eagles and his own appreciation for Philly sports fans. He also emphasized the need to invest in infrastructure and rebuild America, creating jobs and opportunities for all. President Biden discussed the importance of American leadership in the world and the need to restore faith in the country's ability to accomplish great things. He highlighted the progress made in healthcare, including lowering the cost of insulin and capping out-of-pocket expenses for Medicare recipients. He also mentioned the importance of fair taxation and paying for investments in a responsible manner. Finally, President Biden stressed the need to contrast his administration's policies with those of the Republican Party, particularly the extreme MAGA wing. He concluded by taking questions from the audience.